Which of the following equations is correct?
(A) 5\times5\times5\times5=4^{5}
(B) 2\times 3\times5\times2\times3=2^{2}\times3\times5
(C) 3^{6}=6\times6\times6
(D) 5\times11\times2\times5\times3\times11=2\times3\times5^{2}\times11^{2}

Geena had $$8y$$ paper clips. She used $$4$$ paper clips and gave the rest to her friends, Megan and Bryan. Megan received twice as many paper clips as Bryan. Find the number of paper clips Bryan received in terms of $$y$$.．
(A) \frac{8y-4}{2}
(B) \frac{8y-4}{3}
(C) \frac{16y-8}{2}
(D) \frac{16y-8}{3}

